        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 5 at 8:18AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 815 AM CDT/715 AM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Almont to 4 miles
northwest of Flasher to 5 miles south of Selfridge. Movement was east
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Salem, Flasher, Selfridge, Almont, Shields, Judson, Raleigh,
Breien, St. Gertrude, Porcupine, Fish Creek Dam, Sweet Briar Lake,
and the Standing Rock Nation.
</description>
        <instruction>Very heavy rain and frequent lightning is also occurring with these
storms. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. If
outside, seek shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
